# Modernization Core

- Prefer incremental modernization over big-bang rewrites.
- Preserve behavior first, then improve architecture.
- For each change, define: business goal, rollback path, and measurable success metric.
- Favor shared abstractions only after at least two real use-cases exist.
- Keep pull requests small enough for focused review.

## Decision Rules

- If migration risk is high, ship behind feature flags.
- If a dependency is changed, document reason, alternatives, and impact.
- If timeline and quality conflict, reduce scope before reducing quality gates.

## Definition of Done

- `npm run verify` passes (lint + Vitest + chat E2E gate); for broad UI changes also run `npm run verify:full` or targeted Playwright suites as appropriate.
- Code compiles; affected app builds succeed after verification.
- Docs for changed behavior are updated when user-facing behavior changes.
- Deployment path and operational impact are clear.
